TTWO - Market Data & News
TTWO - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

Shares of Take-Two Interactive Software Inc. (TTWO) broke into a new 52-week high yesterday, hitting a peak of $82.79. 
Shares closed at $79.71 after opening at $81.80 for a move of -2.15%. The company now has a market cap of $8.28 billion.

Investors and traders can learn a lot about a stock’s momentum when it sets a new 52-week high. As an example, bullish investors view a company hitting its highest price in a year as a sign of 
momentum and may interpret it as a signal to buy. On the other hand, bearish investors could view a new 52-week high as a signal of the end of a strong run, with the stock possibly peaking out 
before an impending period of decline.


For Take-Two Interactive Software Inc., the new 52-week high came on volume of 2.8 million. The stock has a float of 103.84 million shares and average daily volume of $2.05 million. It has a 
50-day SMA of $75.04 and a 200-day SMA of $59.13. Take-Two Interactive Software Inc. now has a P/E ratio of 118.1.

For a complete fundamental analysis analysis of Take-Two Interactive Software Inc., check out Equities.com’s Stock Valuation Analysis report 
for 
TTWO.
